        "data_source": "Substory conclusions: S1 (C-slot) + S2 (C-slot) + S3 (C-slot) + S4 (C-slot) + S5 (C-slot); narrative/00_throughline.md; REPORT.md \u00a7Future directions"
      },
      "speaker_notes_seed": "The OM proteome replication is the immediate near-term experiment \u2014 the data provider already has it slated for summer 2026, and it nails down the two post-hoc findings (lptC2 transcript-protein decoupling and Pal-Tol induction) before publication. The SigU regulon characterization is the longer novel arc: no Caulobacter SigU regulon exists in the literature, and the late ChvI cohort from NB03 gives us a ready candidate target list to validate.\n\n**Sources:** Substory conclusions: S1 (C-slot) + S2 (C-slot) + S3 (C-slot) + S4 (C-slot) + S5 (C-slot); narrative/00_throughline.md; REPORT.md \u00a7Future directions",
