      "speaker_notes": "RB-TnSeq is the primary fitness workhorse \u2014 198 Caulobacter experiments across 3943 genes, grounding the phenotype-bearing rate calibration and the Fur-regulon enrichment test (Findings 1\u20132); PaperBLAST is the annotation backbone spanning DEG characterization through the comparative species presence/absence panel (Findings 3\u20136); GO terms (NB03) characterized ChvI phase themes, Pfam (NB05) anchored the PG-remodeling gene set, and PubMed + isolates supported literature anchoring and strain references. RefSeq (external, NCBI) confirmed the NB06b comparative absence calls that make Finding 6 robust against PaperBLAST's ~80% false-negative rate for Caulobacter lipid A genes. All 10 notebooks draw from the single `beril` tenant \u2014 this project did not span multiple BERDL tenants.",
